post_text: W.C. Petty hosted their 1st Annual Book Swap in honor of Read Across America Week and what a page turning experience it was! Students in Kindergarten through 5th grade were encouraged to look under their beds, on and behind their bookshelves, and all around their home for books they have outgrown and were looking for a new home. The success of this new tradition was proudly put together by our wildly creative Student Council made up of student representatives and teacher facilitators. Thank you to all of our families who passed on their book collections to share the love of reading with others!

post_text: Members of the Antioch Fire Department have begun visiting our kindergarten classrooms. Showing off their gear and talking to our students about fire safety, these firefighters have made quite an impression on our youngest students. Thank you, Antioch Fire Department, for coming to visit, for teaching us, and for keeping us safe!

post_text: It is with great excitement that the District 34 Board of Education announces that Dr. Bradford Hubbard will be joining our learning community as the new Superintendent of Schools. He will officially be starting this July, to begin the 2020-2021 school year. So, in the coming months, if you happen to see a new (or perhaps familiar) face on one of our school campuses as he familiarizes himself with the district, please join us in welcoming him to District 34! shared_text:
Antioch Upper Grade School
October 4, 2019 at 3:52 PM ·

Update regarding email:

At 1:57PM on October 4th 2019 a fraudulent email labeled “Your Invoice for $1420 is ready” was sent to all district staff and parents. This email originated from a breach of the Constant Contact account which D34 uses to send emails to the community and staff. This external service was breached and compromised which resulted in this incident. At no time were any of Antioch District 34’s servers or systems compromised. Please know that the safety and security of our students—and data about them—is a top priority for the District. The District is now working with Constant Contact to get an explanation of how this happened and what they are doing to ensure it doesn’t happen again. We apologize for the inconvenience.

post_text:
Join the Band!

Is your 4th or 5th Grade student interested in joining the D34 Elementary Band? We would love for you to join us and hop on the “Band Wagon!” The elementary band teachers have visited all 4th grade classrooms this week to share information about the elementary band program in D34. We are also talking to any interested 5th grade student who is new to band.

A short informational parent meeting is on Tuesday, 8/27 at 7pm in the AUGS Café (please us the 7N entrance).
Students will be fitted with instruments by appointment on Wednesday, 8/28 and Thursday, 8/29. Please email Mrs. Mack at cmack@antioch34.com with questions!
